175 (c) A person who verifies to the board that he or she is employed in this state as a
176 radiologist assistant as of the effective date of this article shall by operation of law be
177 licensed to practice as a radiologist assistant in this state on July 1, 2025.
178 43-34-335.
179 (a) A radiologist may use the services of a radiologist assistant under the on site direct
180 supervision of such radiologist, provided that such radiologist assistant is duly qualified
181 and licensed pursuant to this article.
182 (b) A radiologist assistant shall not interpret images, make diagnoses, or prescribe
183 medications or therapies.
184 (c) Any rules and regulations adopted by the board pertaining to the scope of practice as
